{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"goldleaf-calorific-topi","description":"## Why\n`test_silent_success.py::test_reask_prompt_includes_bounded_prior_output` pins the private\nconstant `_FAULTY_OUTPUT_SNIPPET_CHARS == 2000` and greps `inspect.getsource(_pai_structured)`\nfor prompt fragments (`:92-99`); it never runs a retry, so it passes even if the reask is\nbroken. VALIDATED. The suite already uses `FunctionModel` seams, so a behavioral test is\nstraightforward.\n\n## What\nDrive `_pai_structured` with a model that returns malformed output on turn 1, capture the\nturn-2 request, and assert the reask embeds the prior reply, bounded, and marked truncated\nonly when necessary.\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/test_silent_success.py`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Test forces a malformed first reply and captures the actual second model request.\n- [ ] Asserts prior output is present, bounded to the cap, and `[truncated]` appears only\n      when the prior output exceeded the cap.\n- [ ] No assertion on the private constant name or on `_pai_structured` source text.\n- [ ] `make test` green.","id":"d5f0-b85f-aa56-46b0","parent_id":"bf50-2131-271b-4fdc","priority":2,"tags":["p1","llm-runtime","change-detector"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Replace bounded-reask test with a behavioral capture of the retry request"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783784815016306001,"uuid":"1aa07915-ec03-4dcf-8449-47b632ce3e6b"}